{"word":"ἐρέικω","slug":"ἐρέικω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐρέικω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to rend</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>: <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>ἐρεικόμενος περὶ δουρί</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to bruise, pound, shatter</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> only in aor2 <el>ἤρικον</el>, <i>to be rent, to shiver</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}